{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777066814330,"sessionID":"ses_23e918094ffeeU5LzpA5S2I6KL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"call_omo_agent","callID":"call_muY82R6p4fMutcFhTwB0Q8jM","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore workspace capabilities","prompt":"You are helping with project requirement analysis in D:\\agent_workspace. Quickly inspect the workspace structure around capability-library, mycli, and any task/task-hall related implementations or conventions. Focus on: 1) existing capability patterns, 2) any task-hall related directories/files, 3) how analysis/report tasks are typically represented. Return a concise synthesis with concrete file paths.","run_in_background":false,"session_id":"","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"The user wants me to inspect the workspace structure around capability-library, mycli, and task/task-hall related implementations. Let me start by exploring the directory structure and looking for relevant patterns.\n\nI'll need to:\n1. Look at the overall structure of capability-library\n2. Examine mycli structure\n3. Search for task-hall related directories/files\n4. Look for analysis/report task patterns\n\nLet me start with multiple parallel operations to gather information efficiently.\n\n\n<analysis>\n**Literal Request**: Inspect workspace structure around capability-library, mycli, and task/task-hall related implementations\n**Actual Need**: Understand existing capability patterns, find task-hall related code, and see how analysis/report tasks are represented\n**Success Looks Like**: Concrete file paths showing patterns for capabilities, task-hall structure, and analysis task conventions\n</analysis>\n\nLet me explore the workspace structure in parallel:\n\n\nGrep isn't available. Let me use glob and bash ls instead to explore the structure.\n\n\nLet me look at the capability-library directory structure, and also search for task-hall related content more carefully.\n\n\nNow let me look deeper into the key directories - especially skill-library to understand capability patterns, and AGENT-TEAM for task-hall related content.\n\n\nI found task-hall directories. Let me look at the task-hall structure in both locations:\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\task-hall\\`\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\`\n\nLet me read these and also look at some skill packages to understand capability patterns.\n\n\nLet me read the key files to understand the patterns.\n\n\nNow I have a comprehensive view of the workspace. Let me also look at a few more capability patterns and see the task-hall scripts.\n\n\n\nLet me also check a couple more key capability patterns and the task-hall scripts:\n\n\nNow I have a comprehensive view. Let me also quickly check the skill-library structure for a representative skill to understand the capability pattern, and see what SKILL.md looks like in a few other skills for comparison.\n\n\nNow I have enough context to provide a concise synthesis.\n\n\n<results>\n<files>\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\` - Primary CLI integration layer (mycli.ps1, cli.package.json conventions)\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\` - task-hall implementation as a mycli package\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\cli.package.json` - Package registry: 18 commands (init, submit-request, claim, review-submission, tasks, show, edit, etc.)\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\scripts\\task-hall.ps1` - Core runtime script\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\README.md` - Full protocol documentation (665 lines)\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\task-hall\\SKILL.md` - Skill contract for task-hall usage by agents\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\common\\cli.ps1` - Core runtime for package lookup, help rendering, and command execution\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\AGENT-TEAM\\部门\\报告部.md` - Placeholder for \"报告部\" (Reporting/Analysis department) with the tagline \"负责让你看清全局\"\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\AGENT-TEAM\\部门\\报告部\\` - Empty directory under 报告部\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\` - 35 skill packages; each typically has SKILL.md as primary contract\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\AGENT-TEAM\\` - Team structure docs: 部门/ (报告部, 工程部, 机会部, 交互部, 进化部, 评估部, 运营部), models.md, agents.md, etc.\n</files>\n\n<answer>\n\n## Capability Patterns\n\n1. **Package-as-directory with `cli.package.json` + `README.md`** — Every mycli package follows this pattern:\n   - `cli.package.json` defines the package name, summary, source path, and a `commands[]` array mapping command names to absolute-path `entry` scripts with `prefixArgs` for sub-dispatch.\n   - `README.md` serves as the `--help` source for the package.\n   - Example: `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\cli.package.json` (297 lines, 18 commands)\n\n2. **SKILL.md as the primary skill contract** — Skill packages under `skill-library/` use `SKILL.md` as the main contract. Packages may also have `package.json`, `pyproject.toml`, `README.md`, etc.\n\n3. **mycli runtime in `common/cli.ps1`** — 966-line core runtime handles package discovery by scanning directories, reading `cli.package.json`, and dispatching to absolute-path entry scripts with `prefixArgs`.\n\n4. **Skill index via `mycli skill-library`** — Registry at `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\skill-library\\registry.json` stores skill metadata (name, description, skillMdPath, skillRootPath). Registration done via `mycli skill-library register`.\n\n---\n\n## Task-Hall Implementation\n\n**`task-hall` is a first-class mycli package** (not under `skill-library/`):\n\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\cli.package.json` | 18 commands registered |\n| `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\README.md` | Full protocol doc (665 lines) — frontdesk-v0.2 + reviewer-v0.1 |\n| `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\scripts\\task-hall.ps1` | Implementation of all 18 commands |\n| `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\state\\` | Task storage (listings.json, events.jsonl, per-task dirs) |\n\n**Task lifecycle**: `draft` → `listed` → `claimed` → `done` / `cancelled` / `archived`\n\n**Task request standard** — JSON with `request_type` (scheduled/trigger/custom), title, description, context, expected_output, constraints, optional target_path/schedule/trigger/priority/tags.\n\n**Claim gate** — Model tiers: `nano < cheap < standard < strong < expert`; frontdesk agent enforces `## 领取门槛` in task Markdown.\n\n**Reviewer protocol** — Four decisions: `complete`, `return_to_agent`, `relist_as_is`, `revise_and_relist`.\n\n**Agent configs** (external, referenced):\n- `C:\\Users\\38188\\.config\\opencode\\agent\\task-hall-frontdesk.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\38188\\.config\\opencode\\agent\\task-hall-reviewer.md`\n\n---\n\n## How Analysis/Report Tasks Are Represented\n\n**Analysis tasks** follow the task-hall workflow: submit via JSON request → frontdesk review → task Markdown with `## 领取门槛` → agent claim → work → Markdown report → reviewer decision.\n\n**\"报告部\" (Reporting Department)** exists as a placeholder under `D:\\agent_workspace\\AGENT-TEAM\\部门\\` with the tagline \"负责让你看清全局\" (Responsible for giving you a clear view of the whole). Its directory is currently empty. The report department is meant to consume/produce reports, but no analysis/report skill or task-hall skill package exists yet under `skill-library/` specifically for analysis.\n\n**Task report Markdown structure** (from task-hall SKILL.md):\n```\n## 任务结论 (完成/部分完成/受阻/无法完成)\n## 完成内容\n## 未完成内容\n## 产物路径\n## 验证结果\n## 遇到的问题\n## 是否需要继续\n```\n\n---\n\n## Notable Observations\n\n- **Two `task-hall` entries**: One is a **mycli package** (`mycli/task-hall/` — the runtime implementation) and another is a **skill package** (`skill-library/task-hall/SKILL.md` — the agent-facing contract). They are distinct: the skill contract explains *how agents should use* task-hall; the mycli package is *the tool itself*.\n- **`skill-library/` has 35 packages** but no explicit \"analysis\" or \"report generation\" skill — this could be a gap if you want a reusable analysis capability surfaced through `mycli skill-library`.\n- **No skill for 报告部** yet — the department exists in org docs but has no corresponding skill package or mycli command entry.\n</answer>\n\n<next_steps>\n- If you want to build an analysis/report capability: model it after `task-hall` SKILL.md pattern (publish JSON request → agent claim → Markdown report → reviewer decision), or create a new skill under `skill-library/` with its own SKILL.md and `cli.package.json` entry\n- If you want to formalize 报告部: create `skill-library/report-analysis/SKILL.md` and register it, or add commands to an existing mycli package\n- Ready to proceed — just indicate which direction you want to go\n</next_steps>\n\n<task_metadata>\nsession_id: ses_23e9136f4ffexZdZ6lE4k5mbhR\n</task_metadata>\n\nto continue: task(session_id=\"ses_23e9136f4ffexZdZ6lE4k5mbhR\", load_skills=[], run_in_background=false, prompt=\"...\")","metadata":{"truncated":false},"title":"","time":{"start":1777066756341,"end":1777066814329}},"id":"prt_dc16ec8f1001Uv14Y25XU7dt62","sessionID":"ses_23e918094ffeeU5LzpA5S2I6KL","messageID":"msg_dc16e7feb001CkDlb0upSK1dov"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777066839301,"sessionID":"ses_23e918094ffeeU5LzpA5S2I6KL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"call_omo_agent","callID":"call_oVFH5AAUmWoud2v4nXLYm4Oh","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore skill library reuse","prompt":"Inspect D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library for existing reusable skills/capabilities relevant to project analysis, task intake, workflow orchestration, and reporting. Focus on mycli packages and skill-library directories; exclude noisy vendor dirs. Return concise findings with concrete paths and likely reusable components.","run_in_background":false,"session_id":"","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"The user wants me to inspect the capability-library directory for reusable skills/capabilities related to:\n1. Project analysis\n2. Task intake\n3. Workflow orchestration\n4. Reporting\n\nThey want me to focus on mycli packages and skill-library directories, and exclude noisy vendor directories.\n\nLet me start by exploring the structure and finding relevant skills.\n\n\n<analysis>\n**Literal Request**: Inspect `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library` for reusable skills/capabilities in project analysis, task intake, workflow orchestration, and reporting.\n\n**Actual Need**: Find concrete, reusable components in the mycli package system and skill-library that could be leveraged for project analysis, task intake, workflow orchestration, and reporting. User wants actionable findings with paths.\n\n**Success Looks Like**: List of relevant skill packages with their paths, descriptions, and identification of which are reusable for the stated purposes.\n</analysis>\n\n\nThe grep tool failed because \"rg\" (ripgrep) isn't available. Let me use glob and read to explore the structure. Let me also look at the mycli package structure and skill-library more carefully.\n\n\nGood, I found the directory structures. Now I need to read the SKILL.md files from the most relevant skill packages. Based on the names, the most relevant ones for project analysis, task intake, workflow orchestration, and reporting would be:\n\n- agent-workflow (looks highly relevant for workflow orchestration)\n- project-manager (project analysis/management)\n- project-skill-manager (project management)\n- skill-creator (skill creation)\n- workflow_engine (workflow orchestration)\n- task-hall (task intake/hall)\n- agent-cli (agent CLI - relevant for project analysis)\n- cli-anything (CLI anything - might be useful)\n- skill-vetter (might be useful for reporting)\n- summarize-1.0.0 (reporting)\n\nLet me read several of these in parallel.\n\n\nNow let me also check the mycli packages that are most directly relevant: `project-manager`, `agent-workflow`, `task-hall`, `cli-anything`. Let me also look at the `agent-all-in-one` and `agent-system-rules` directories mentioned at the top level.\n\n\nNow let me also check the `opencli` and `cli-anything` packages since they could have relevant capabilities.\n\n\nNow I have enough information to provide a comprehensive, actionable report. Let me compile the findings.\n\nThe key reusable components I found for the four focus areas:\n\n**Project Analysis:**\n- `project-manager` (skill + mycli package) - full project lifecycle management with status tracking, task/next-action management, context entries\n- `project-skill-manager` (skill-library) - project state management (todo/done/sustained/skill_dependent), project-skill relationship management\n\n**Task Intake:**\n- `task-hall` (mycli package) - full task intake workflow with frontdesk agent, task publishing, claiming, reporting, reviewer decisions\n- `agent-workflow` (skill + mycli package) - multi-step workflow orchestration with review gates\n\n**Workflow Orchestration:**\n- `agent-workflow` (skill + mycli package) - step-based durable workflows with state, listener/webhook waiting, review gates, transitions\n- `workflow_engine` (skill-library) - `workflow.json`-driven workflow engine with para_id_map parameter propagation, dynamic node expansion, breakpoint resume, web UI\n\n**Reporting:**\n- `task-hall` (mycli package) - task report submission and reviewer decisions (complete, return_to_agent, relist_as_is, revise_and_relist)\n- `summarize-1.0.0` (skill-library) - URL/file/YouTube summarization CLI\n- `self-improving-agent-3.0.5` (skill-library) - continuous improvement logging with error tracking, learnings promotion\n\nOther notable:\n- `skill-creator` - guidance for creating new skills\n- `agent-cli` (skill + mycli package) - unified agent CLI surface for opencode/harness/codex\n\n\n- `skill-vetter-1.0.0` - security vetting for new skills\n- `elite-longterm-memory-1.2.3` - long-term memory system\n\nLet me structure the output properly.\n\n\n<results>\n<files>\n- D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\project-manager\\SKILL.md - full project lifecycle management (finite/ongoing, lifecycle/phase/activity/health/delivery axes, task/next-action/context tracking, agent handoff guides)\n- D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\project-manager\\cli.package.json - mycli entry point for project-manager; source at D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\agent-system-rules\\project-manager\n- D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\task-hall\\SKILL.md - task intake surface with frontdesk-v0.2 JSON requests, claim gates, reviewer-v0.1 reports, structured task lifecycle\n- D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\cli.package.json - mycli task-hall commands: submit-request, claim, review-submission, tasks, show, done, cancel, archive\n- D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\agent-workflow\\SKILL.md - durable multi-step workflow framework with workflow.json, step scaffolding, listener/webhook waiting, review gates, state persistence\n- D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\agent-workflow\\cli.package.json - mycli agent-workflow: init, scaffold, validate, graph, start-run, inject-event, status, review-step\n- D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\workflow_engine\\SKILL.md - workflow.json-driven engine with para_id_map propagation, dynamic node expansion, breakpoint resume, Web UI, action.py executor\n- D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\summarize-1.0.0\\SKILL.md - summarize CLI for URLs, PDFs, images, audio, YouTube; cross-platform npm package\n- D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\self-improving-agent-3.0.5\\SKILL.md - continuous improvement logging with structured error/learnings/feature_request entries, promotion workflow to CLAUDE.md/AGENTS.md/SOUL.md/TOOLS.md\n- D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\skill-creator\\SKILL.md - skill authoring methodology: SKILL.md structure, bundled scripts/references/assets, progressive disclosure, packaging\n- D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\agent-cli\\cli.package.json - unified agent CLI surface: agents, current, sync, run, session, schedule, mount, native, codex-auto, agent, source\n- D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\skill-library\\cli.package.json - skill discovery: skills, search, register; registry at D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\skill-library\\registry.json\n</files>\n\n<answer>\n**Project Analysis**\n- `project-manager` (skill + mycli package): Mature project registry with multi-axis status (lifecycle/phase/activity/health/delivery), per-project task lists, next-action queues, dynamic context entries, and agent-takeover guides. Project types include capability, workflow, coding, research, documentation, ops, experiment, external_repo, meta.\n- `project-skill-manager` (skill-library): Complementary model using todo/done/sustained/skill_dependent states; manages project-skill relationships and固化 (solidification) workflow.\n\n**Task Intake**\n- `task-hall` (mycli package): Full task coordination layer — submit task via frontdesk-v0.2 JSON request, model-tier claim gates, structured Markdown task specs, reviewer-v0.1 task reports. Reviewer decisions: complete, return_to_agent, relist_as_is, revise_and_relist.\n- `agent-workflow` (mycli package): Supports task intake as step-based workflows with explicit review gates and listener/webhook waiting points.\n\n**Workflow Orchestration**\n- `agent-workflow` (skill + mycli): Durable step-based workflows with persisted state, workflow.json-driven step scaffolding, listener/webhook events, review gates, and run status inspection. Best for semi-fixed multi-step agent processes.\n- `workflow_engine` (skill-library): Python workflow engine driven by workflow.json with para_id_map parameter propagation (1:1 and 1:many), dynamic node expansion from action return values, breakpoint resume via input.json/output.json, Web UI for state inspection/editing, and scripts.llm for LLM calls within nodes. Best for data-processing pipelines with multiple stages.\n\n**Reporting**\n- `task-hall review-submission`: Structured Markdown task reports with completion/partially-done/blocked sections, verification results, artifact paths, and reviewer disposition.\n- `summarize-1.0.0`: CLI tool for summarizing URLs, files, PDFs, images, audio, YouTube — useful for generating digest reports.\n- `self-improving-agent-3.0.5`: Error/learnings logging with structured entries (ERRORS.md, LEARNINGS.md, FEATURE_REQUESTS.md) and promotion workflow to workspace governance files.\n\n**Supporting Infrastructure**\n- `skill-creator`: SKILL.md authoring guide with progressive disclosure patterns and bundled scripts/references/assets conventions.\n- `skill-vetter-1.0.0`: Security vetting protocol before installing external skills.\n- `agent-cli` (mycli): Unified surface over opencode/harness/codex for running coding agents, sessions, scheduling.\n- `elite-longterm-memory-1.2.3`: Long-term memory system (not inspected in detail but in the skill-library index).\n</answer>\n\n<next_steps>\nTo use these components:\n1. For project tracking: `mycli project-manager init <path> --id <id> --name <name> --type <type> --mode finite|ongoing --register`\n2. For task intake workflow: `mycli task-hall submit-request <task-request.json>` with frontdesk JSON schema\n3. For durable multi-step orchestration: `mycli agent-workflow init <path> --workflow-id <id> --name <name>` then scaffold/validate/graph\n4. For pipeline-style processing: leverage workflow_engine's workflow.json + para_id_map + dynamic node expansion\n5. For reporting: use task-hall review-submission with the Markdown report template from its SKILL.md\n</next_steps>\n</results>\n\n<task_metadata>\nsession_id: ses_23e9136f2ffeOUCrlEX7ha5aBA\n</task_metadata>\n\nto continue: task(session_id=\"ses_23e9136f2ffeOUCrlEX7ha5aBA\", load_skills=[], run_in_background=false, prompt=\"...\")","metadata":{"truncated":false},"title":"","time":{"start":1777066756346,"end":1777066839300}},"id":"prt_dc16ec8f6001Ge41kc05BQpe9F","sessionID":"ses_23e918094ffeeU5LzpA5S2I6KL","messageID":"msg_dc16e7feb001CkDlb0upSK1dov"}}
